# Updating your service to use the new brand

In June 2025, GOV.UK started to refresh the brand across its products and services.

The changes affect these components:

- [GOV.UK header](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/header/)
- [GOV.UK footer](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/footer/)
- [Cookie banner](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/cookie-banner/)
- [Service navigation](https://design-system.service.gov.uk/components/service-navigation/)

## If you’re using GOV.UK Frontend v6

If you're using GOV.UK Frontend 6.0.0 or higher then the refreshed brand will be applied to your service by default and you don't need to do anything.

## If you're using an older version of GOV.UK Frontend

If you're using an older version of GOV.UK Frontend such as v5 or v4, we recommend upgrading to v6 by following our [guidance on staying up to date](../staying-up-to-date/).

If you are unable to upgrade, you can read the [v5 guidance on using the new brand](../v5/brand-refresh-changes/) for how to apply the brand to older versions of frontend.

Applying the initial brand refresh to a service using older version of GOV.UK Frontend will not apply further changes from the refreshed brand, such as the new colour palette. Therefore we recommend upgrading to the latest version of GOV.UK Frontend as soon as possible.
